<paragraph blockId="25.[136,1451,1058,1193]" pageId="25" pageNumber="236">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,294,1094,1120]" pageId="25" pageNumber="236">Notes:—</emphasis>
This proliferous species with purplish flowers is similar to the also proliferous 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Luer" authorityYear="1982" baseAuthorityName="Ames" baseAuthorityYear="1923" box="[1168,1307,1094,1120]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Myoxanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="25" pageNumber="236" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="scandens">
<emphasis box="[1168,1307,1094,1120]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="236">M. scandens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and the nonproliferous 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Luer &amp; Hirtz" authorityYear="1992" box="[266,419,1130,1156]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Myoxanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="25" pageNumber="236" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="antennifer">
<emphasis box="[266,419,1130,1156]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="236">M. antennifer</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. It is recognized by acuminate lateral sepals 
<emphasis box="[923,946,1131,1156]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="236">vs</emphasis>
. acute in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Luer" authorityYear="1982" baseAuthorityName="Ames" baseAuthorityYear="1923" box="[1056,1197,1130,1156]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Myoxanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="25" pageNumber="236" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="scandens">
<emphasis box="[1056,1197,1130,1156]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="236">M. scandens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Luer &amp; Hirtz" authorityYear="1992" box="[1251,1404,1130,1156]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Myoxanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="25" pageNumber="236" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="antennifer">
<emphasis box="[1251,1404,1130,1156]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="236">M. antennifer</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and the fimbriate margin of the petals 
<emphasis box="[517,540,1167,1192]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="236">vs</emphasis>
. margins shortly ciliate in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Luer" authorityYear="1982" baseAuthorityName="Ames" baseAuthorityYear="1923" box="[840,980,1166,1192]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Myoxanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="25" pageNumber="236" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="scandens">
<emphasis box="[840,980,1166,1192]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="236">M. scandens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and entire in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Luer &amp; Hirtz" authorityYear="1992" box="[1133,1286,1166,1192]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Myoxanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="25" pageNumber="236" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="antennifer">
<emphasis box="[1133,1286,1166,1192]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="236">M. antennifer</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
